texts.text: >Everyone sullenly gathers at the hide-out, minus Gakuto.
The serial bombings have brought the economy to a standstill.
Police have been inundated with complaints from citizens...
This ain't good...
Everyone's on edge. Crime rates have rocketed globally,
and mysterious incidents are occurring that remain unresolved.
These "mysterious incidents" look like the work of rogue demons.
But they're occurring a lot more frequently than before.
In other words... things still aren't back to normal.
But we did manage to solve the serial bomber case, right?
We destroyed the place manufacturing Homunculus Bombs, but...
We can't exactly go public about it... it's a tricky situation.
What? Why?
There's two problems. First, Homunculus Bombs can't be made public
Oh, I see.
Yeah, it's better the world doesn't know about that tech.
But the fuzz are gonna announce that a "special explosive" was used.
Then it's case closed, right?
There's one other problem.
Joshua Hawk...
Bingo. We let him get away. And that's a problem y'know?
He could start making Homunculus Bombs again at any time.
If another incident happens after this one is closed...
Peoples faith in the police would be shattered.
Oh, yeah, that would be a problem.
Which is why we gotta tie up all the loose ends ASAP.
True. You can even see the effect here in Akiba's streets.
This place used to be more fun. Bustling, full of life.
Let's make it that way again.
Hey, I like it quiet.
>Jeng looks at you, his face lighting up in a gentle smile.
...Yes. Let's make things the way they used to be.
A bustling town, full of culture, where people can smile.
Full of culture? You mean full of nerd culture?
You could say that.
So, it's decided.
I want to take back our streets so we can all enjoy them again.

...You're right.
That would be nice.
...Yeah. Yeah it would be.
I get it. Honestly, sometimes the crowds can be overwhelming.
I don't hate how quiet the town is at the moment.
The number of tasteless tv shows has dropped too, which is nice.
You shouldn't say things like that.
As it is, Akiba is too lonely...
>As everyone stands silent, an unexpected visitor appears.
It's just me, Seiran Saikawa. How is everyone doing?
Why are you using your full name?
Well, some people here treat me like a stranger and never come
visit the Aura Gate. I thought maybe they'd forgotten me.
Hold on... Why does everyone look so glum? What's going on?

It's nothing.
We're all doing fine.
Jeng! It's been too long! Your Japanese has really improved!
Ah, that's...
Thank you very much.
...no witty comeback?
What do you mean?
You know, your usual one.
Sorry but I'm not sure what you mean...
Oh, come on! Your usual comeback! "Your Japanese isn't bad either".
You always use that joke with Shiang, right? Why not with me?
Sorry, but you're a native Japanese speaker, are you not?
Damn it, why do you take things so literally? What's the harm?
I wonder if that's really the problem here.
Sigh, I wish I was Chinese.
People are people. It doesn't matter where you were born.
Sigh. You don't get it.
Hey, Seiran Saikawa. You didn't come here just to shoot the shit.
Ah, that's right. I have some info on that thing you asked.
"That thing"?
I asked Seiran to dig up some dirt on Vanitas for us.
To tell you the truth...
I had absolutely no idea what you were talking about at first!
Seiran, I'll say this only once.
Give it to us straight and don't draw things out. It pisses me off.
You see, I came across the word "Vanitas" while researching something else.
To be honest, that something else was far more important to me.
The Dragon Stream pollution has gotten worse. And recently, too.
What does that mean?
Joshua Hawk did say that that was the goal of the serial bombings.
But at the time, I didn't understand what he meant...
I think a quick lesson is in order.
The Dragon Stream is the flow of the Earth's energy.
The Chinese have utilized this energy since ancient times.
China is great. Only China could produce someone like Sammo Hung.
...Although he was born in Hong Kong under British rule.
Anyways, moving on.
Even here in Japan, the placement and shape of important buildings
and towns are chosen based on the Dragon Stream's flow.
Those who touch the Stream even when it's weakened, flourish.
Which brings us to the problem at hand.
News on places affected by the bombings have overlooked it, but
shrines, temples, places with spiritually powerful artefacts...
so-called spiritual power spots have been destroyed one after another.
Due to this, the flow of energy has been disturbed and the Dra...

Hold it.
Don't you think that's strange?
Aren't you mixing up a bunch of different schools?
The Dragon Stream, Feng Shui, Taoism, all come from the same source. The same flow of energy.
Chinese and Japanese cuisine are different, but both are made from the same ingredients, right?

I see.
...You may continue.
If these places were merely destroyed, the flow would recover.
But various elements are mixing and negatively affecting the Stream.
Normally, to affect the Dragon Stream you'd have to change the very lay of the land itself.
But they've used various methods to affect the Stream...
Affecting any towns built on the Dragon Stream in the process.
Could that have something to do with the recent rise in crime?
I believe so. Strange energy flow can be traced to such places.
And that's not all. Disasters may also start breaking out.
What? Why?
The Feng Shui used to suppress such disasters was originally based on this same energy.
If we think of the Earth as a body, the energy flow is its cardiovascular system.

If you mess with that...
You'll end up in hospital!
Exactly.
Earthquakes, fires, storms, plague, it's only a matter of time.
Whoah... this is lookin' bad.
That's why we had Gakuto help to capture those responsible....
And use his "Safe Truth Serum".
...ah that decidedly dangerous lookin' stuff...
That's when we came across the name "Vanitas". Apparently it's like a giant computer.
That's when I finally understood.
Like I said, to affect the Dragon Stream you'd normally need to change the lay of the land.
But what if they used Vanitas to simulate the flow of the Dragon Stream
and work out the best areas to target for maximum effect?
Precisely. Calculating the energy flow would normally require skill, experience and time.
To build just a single town correctly takes decades.
But with Vanitas...
...Bingo. It could be done in a matter of minutes!
So while a small change to the flow would be correctable...
multiple changes all at once means it's too difficult to fix, even for me.
And in the time it would take to calculate a fix, if the damage were to continue...
And if it continues...?
Tokyo... no, all of Japan would be destroyed.
Whoah...
No way...
You strolled in here all playful and now you're dropping truth bombs? This is really serious.
How reliable is this theory of yours? Gimme a figure.
Well, setting aside the question of when it will happen, then...
Then...?
Currently, it's 100% certain.
You can't be serious?!

No way!
100%?!?
We have to get outta here.
We have to do something.
That's a wise decision.
Except that the Acolytes are an international organization.
...so even if we ran for it, they'd eventually...
>Everyone turns to look at you.
...You're right.
That's the spirit! There's no point in losing hope!
There's no point in dying if you still have a bullet in the chamber.
That's right! There's no way this is a 100% certainty!
Hey guys, hold up a sec.
Seiran, if we give this our best shot, what's gonna happen?
If we throw every demon we've got at the Acolytes...

How much can we fix this?
Gimme a figure.
...I said the figure I already gave you was the current one.
That's right, you did!
In other words, it was based on us not doing anything?

Correct, Jeng.
Your Japanese has really improved!
Your... Japanese isn't bad either.
...In other words, it's all up to us.
>Seiran takes out a plane ticket and starts to tear it up.
If you guys had decided to run, I was going to leave Japan tonight.
But it doesn't look like that will be necessary now.
I'll do what I can to slow down the damage to the Dragon Stream.

Hurry, Liberators.
There's not much time left.
>Seiran turns, and leaves.
So it's time for the final boss...
It's time to show 'em that the Liberators ain't messin' around!
Are you guys ready?
Wait a minute...
Let's do this!
Don't go off half-cocked or I'll pop a cap in your ass.
We're good to go. Let's give it our best shot.
Seems like a good time for a gun show!
...why would you...
To help everyone to... how do you say... "get hyped"?
Hmm... that word. I do not think it means what you think it means.
Either way, this can't be good.
Okay, here I go!
Keep your shirt on!
Lol... I was hoping for a quick response from everyone, but
seeing y'all like this is pure hype, man.

Alright, we're doing this!
Try to keep up you guys!
